    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - Front Cover, Vibration Damper, and Gerotor Oil Pump - Cleaning, Inspection,
        and Testing
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Cleaning, Inspection, and Testing</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="clean" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Vibration Damper</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid serious personal injury or possible death, wear safety glasses with side shields when
                        using compressed air for cleaning to reduce the danger from flying debris. Limit the air
                        pressure to 207 kPa (30 psi). See
                        <hotlnk xrefid="safety">"Safety Information</hotlnk>."
                    </para>
                </warning>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not immerse damper in petroleum based solvents. Damage to rubber
                        damping element may result.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <para>Clean vibration damper with soap, water, and a soft parts brush. Dry with filtered compressed air.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
